# Binary Calculator

## Overview

The Binary Calculator is a Java-based application developed as part of the SOFE3980U course assignment. The objective of this project is to implement arithmetic and logical operations on binary numbers using object-oriented programming principles and the Maven build automation tool. The application provides a simple interface for performing operations on binary values while demonstrating software development practices such as modular programming, unit testing, and project management using Maven.

This project also demonstrates the use of JUnit for automated testing, ensuring that each implemented function behaves correctly under different test scenarios. Maven is used to manage project dependencies, compile the source code, execute test cases, package the application, and generate project documentation.

## Features

The Binary Calculator supports the following binary operations:

- Binary Addition
- Bitwise OR
- Bitwise AND
- Binary Multiplication

Each operation accepts two binary numbers as input and returns the resulting binary value.

